amdgpu: skip UVD + VCE entirely on Liverpool/Gladius (no SAMU auth)

After SBL Phase 1 confirmed the SAMU stealth-auths writes from our
context (see checkpoint/docs/research/sbl-port/2026-05-12-stealth-
auth-confirmed.md), there's no software path to bring up UVD or
VCE on PS4 Linux. A18/A19 soft-failed the hw_init step but the
VCPU still ran partial bring-up, and the resulting VA-0x300000000
fault retry rate eventually saturated the IH (2.6M faults/5s
observed during sustained SBL probing on 2026-05-12).

Skip both engines entirely by returning -ENODEV from early_init.
amdgpu's ip-block framework disables the engine — sw_init,
hw_init never run, no VCPU release, no fault storm.

Userspace consequence: software video decode via libavcodec /
software encode via libx264. Acceptable trade for a kernel that
doesn't hang itself.

Signed-off-by: Meerzulee <mirzaali@screeninternational.org>

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/uvd_v4_2.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/uvd_v4_2.c
@@ -96,6 +96,33 @@
 static int uvd_v4_2_early_init(struct amdgpu_ip_block *ip_block)
 {
 	struct amdgpu_device *adev = ip_block->adev;
+
+	/*
+	 * v76e-DISABLE-UVD: short-circuit UVD entirely on Liverpool/Gladius.
+	 *
+	 * After all the A-arc + SBL work, we've confirmed Sony's UVD firmware
+	 * cannot be brought up from PSFree's ring 0 — it needs SAMU-signed
+	 * SMU writes (see checkpoint/docs/research/sbl-port/2026-05-12-stealth-
+	 * auth-confirmed.md). A18 soft-failed hw_init but the VCPU still
+	 * runs partial bring-up; under sustained SBL-probe activity it ends
+	 * up retrying its hardcoded VA 0x300000000 access at a rate that
+	 * saturates the IH ring (2.6M faults/5s observed on 2026-05-12).
+	 *
+	 * Skip UVD entirely by returning -ENODEV from early_init — amdgpu's
+	 * ip-block framework disables the engine and never calls sw_init /
+	 * hw_init. No VCPU release, no fault storm, no soft-fail dance.
+	 *
+	 * Userspace consequence: software video decode via libavcodec.
+	 * Acceptable trade until SBL auth is cracked (likely never via
+	 * software-only paths).
+	 */
+	if (adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL ||
+	    adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS) {
+		DRM_INFO("ps4 uvd: skipping UVD entirely on Liverpool/Gladius "
+			 "(no SAMU auth -> no functional UVD; avoids fault storm)\n");
+		return -ENODEV;
+	}
+
 	adev->uvd.num_uvd_inst = 1;
 
 	uvd_v4_2_set_ring_funcs(adev);

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/vce_v2_0.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/vce_v2_0.c
@@ -408,6 +408,18 @@
 {
 	struct amdgpu_device *adev = ip_block->adev;
 
+	/*
+	 * v76e-DISABLE-VCE: sibling of the UVD disable in uvd_v4_2.c. Same
+	 * reasoning — Sony's VCE firmware needs SAMU-signed SMU writes we
+	 * can't perform, A19 soft-fail wasn't enough under sustained SBL
+	 * activity. Skip the engine entirely.
+	 */
+	if (adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL ||
+	    adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS) {
+		DRM_INFO("ps4 vce: skipping VCE entirely on Liverpool/Gladius\n");
+		return -ENODEV;
+	}
+
 	adev->vce.num_rings = 2;
 
 	vce_v2_0_set_ring_funcs(adev);
